id: output-display-policy
severity: critical
description: "All new prompts and outputs created by any agent must be displayed in full on the terminal"
guard: "ALL NEW PROMPTS AND OUTPUTS CREATED BY ANY AGENT MUST BE DISPLAYED IN FULL ON THE TERMINAL. Outputs written to files must also be printed to stdout."
rules:
  - Every new prompt or output must be visible on the terminal
  - The terminal is the primary delivery channel, not the filesystem
  - Writing to a file alone is NOT sufficient - must also display
